  "articleSummary": "**Summary:**  \nThis tutorial introduces JavaScript Promises as a structured approach to handling asynchronous operations, emphasizing their role in managing success/failure outcomes. Key points include creating Promises via `Promise.resolve()` or the constructor pattern, leveraging native APIs like `fetch`, and using `.then()/.catch()` for result handling. The article highlights common pitfalls (e.g., unhandled rejections) and utility methods like `Promise.all()` and `Promise.race()`. Framed as a beginner-friendly guide, it uses code examples and a success/failure flow diagram to clarify concepts, targeting developers new to asynchronous programming.",
